SENTENCE e .
SENTENCE the world was coming out of an ice age  .
SENTENCE and with that came increased seasonality ,  that is ,  the summers became warmer ,  and the winters actually became colder .
SENTENCE these extreme shifts would have put a lot of stress on the bodies of animals that were used to a more moderate range of temperatures .
SENTENCE but the most important impact of this increased seasonality may very well have been its effect on the distribution of plants .
SENTENCE today we take for granted that there horizontal bands of plant communities .
