SENTENCE uh ,  you know ,  i recently read an interesting article about an archaeologist who tried to solve this puzzle with the help of his computer .
SENTENCE what he did was ,  he wrote a computer program to simulate what would happen to mammoth under certain conditions .
SENTENCE say ,  for example ,  there is a drought for a couple of decades ,  or hunters are killing or five percent of the population ,  and so on .
SENTENCE one thing he found was that humans didn't necessarily have to kill these animals in great numbers in order to nudge them toward extinction .
SENTENCE that's because very large animals have a slow rate of reproduction ,  so all you have to do is remove a few young females from the herd ,  and you can ,  fairly quickly ,  significantly reduce the population .
SENTENCE and then he came up with a scenario that combined some hunting by humans with some environmental stress ,  and  bang !
SENTENCE the simulated mammoths were extinct within decades .
SENTENCE so it seems the mixture of hunting and climate change is a likely scenario .
SENTENCE uh ,  of course ,  computer simulations are not a substitute for hard evidence .
